stylometry: Our group project had to do with minimiseing costs at a hospital by finding out how many nurses should be on staff per patient, so that we incur no waiting or liability costs, but also not exceeding necessary amount of nurses so that we are paying unneccesary excess wages. We ran a simulation of a normal distribution and found that the optimal solution would be staffing 1 nurse to 5 patients. This solution gave us the highest min and max profist with a low standard deviation, and we also were incurring 0 waiting and liability costs. I learned a lot about how excel can actually figure out business situations for you. It can tell you how many employees to employ and staff at certain times to produce the best results for your company in terms of profitability and avoiding unneccesary costs.
